ibution function probes\nlarger scales compared to the nearest neighbour distribution function, which is\ninfluenced by details of structures. We also find a linear relation between the\nmean and variance of the spherical contact probability distribution function in\nsimulations and mock galaxies, which could be used as a distinguishing probe of\ncosmological models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Jun 2021 17:50:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Jan 2022 09:51:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-20"}
